What: Meet for meals and drinks at Broadway Tavern; 18+ only event.

Want a break from lectures and labs?Come to our club room, down the hall in room 2.26. This is not a members-only deal; it is available for all computer science students to use. The club sells a variety of cheap food and drink, including pies, sausage rolls, chips, ice creams and chocolates. The club room has a fridge, microwave and kettle that you are free to use, and also has comfy couches, power outlets and wireless coverage if you want to work on your laptop.
About the Computer Science Students' Club

The Computer Science Students' Club (CSSC) runs social and educational events for students in the School of Computer Science and Software Engineering, at the University of Western Australia. The CSSC has a club room in the Computer Science building, near the student computer labs, which sells food and drink, and has a fridge, microwave, couches, and gaming consoles for computer science students to use. The CSSC also runs a number of regular events, including weekly barbecues each Tuesday, staff vs. students soccer matches at the end of each semester, an annual quiz night in the UWA Tav, and occasional LANs.
